        <h1>Albrecht Dürer Watercolor Marker - Features & Benefits</h1>

        <p>The highly pigmented water-based artists' watercolor markers are available in 30 individual colors and also in assorted gift sets. The water soluble inks are highly lightfast and provide excellent watercolor effects on watercolor paper. They are odorless and the inks will not bleed through paper. The Albrecht Dürer Watercolor Markers are of course non-toxic.</p>

        <h2>Product Details</h2>
        <p>The fiber-tip nib is made of polyester. It has a diameter of 3.25mm and the line it can create is between 1-2mm depending on the drawing angle. The brush nib is made of nylon and has a diameter of 5.2mm. Both nibs share one reservoir. The cap, barrel and nib-holders are made of polypropylene/polyethylene. The reservoir is made of polyester.</p>

        <h2>Storage</h2>
        <p>It is recommended to store the pens in a horizontal position to prolong the life and quality of the product when not in use.</p>

        <h2>The Pens Are Not Rehydratable</h2>
        <p>If the cap is accidentally left off for up to 3 hours, the marker will probably "recover" just by itself. In case the cap has been left off for a long period of time, the performance cannot be "revoked" perfectly by adding water or sticking the nibs into a glass of water. This might be possible with a marker based on dyestuff, but not so with a pigmented marker such as this.</p>

        <h2>Watercolor Paper</h2>
        <p>Good drawing results depend on the paper being used. For optimal results we recommend watercolor paper from Canson Montval (300gsm – fine grained) and Hahnemühle Fine Art Britannia (300gsm hot pressed).</p>

